1
00:00:01,651 --> 00:00:06,202
Really, your first connection
substantially with Reality

2
00:00:06,202 --> 00:00:10,078
is hearing from an agent,
a divine agent.

3
00:00:10,078 --> 00:00:12,597
Oh, I’m being grafted.

4
00:00:12,857 --> 00:00:17,647
[Mind: We Have Met the Enemy]

5
00:00:17,757 --> 00:00:22,006
Taking the mind 
as the best advisor of yourself—

6
00:00:22,006 --> 00:00:23,186
not a good idea.

7
00:00:23,816 --> 00:00:28,526
It’s onIy natural that you think that
you are somehow being conned,

8
00:00:28,526 --> 00:00:32,467
but think a little harder and
you’ll realize that this is not a trick.

9
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:36,017
To do an honest assessment
of yourself and say,

10
00:00:36,017 --> 00:00:40,851
“Yes, I’m, in a sense, 
hopeless, helpless.”

11
00:00:40,877 --> 00:00:42,608
You don’t have 
a lot of time,

12
00:00:44,338 --> 00:00:48,618
and, in reality, 
you don’t have a choice.

13
00:00:48,618 --> 00:00:52,586
Now, the most sensible thing to do
would be to get a second opinion.

14
00:00:53,876 --> 00:00:58,527
So, we try to come under the influence
of the revealed truth.

15
00:00:58,527 --> 00:01:01,338
And you say,
“Oh, in Bhagavad-gītā Kṛṣṇa says,

16
00:01:01,338 --> 00:01:03,817
‘Above the senses is the mind.’”

17
00:01:03,817 --> 00:01:09,184
Ok, the mind is higher than the senses,
and it’s the seat of sense experience.

18
00:01:09,184 --> 00:01:12,684
Then He says, 
“Finer than the mind is intelligence.”

19
00:01:12,688 --> 00:01:15,334
Then you say, 
”Ok, now I understand, intelligence—

20
00:01:15,334 --> 00:01:18,910
discriminating factor because the mind 
has no discriminating ability.”

21
00:01:18,910 --> 00:01:22,573
So, we are told, “You need to infuse
the intelligence with dharma-buddhi”—

22
00:01:22,580 --> 00:01:24,660
back to sādhu, śāstra, 
guru, Vaiṣṇav.

23
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:27,516
Finer than intelligence, 
He is saying is what?

24
00:01:27,516 --> 00:01:29,806
“That’s the beginning 
of the ātmā plane”.

25
00:01:29,845 --> 00:01:32,346
That’s where the self is located.

26
00:01:32,394 --> 00:01:37,295
So, if you are viewing the self
from the outside in

27
00:01:37,392 --> 00:01:41,280
and seeing yourself 
in terms of gender,

28
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:46,355
nationality, age—
all these things,

29
00:01:46,395 --> 00:01:51,295
you are not having
a proper glimpse of yourself,

30
00:01:51,295 --> 00:01:54,265
and who you are,
and what is your potential.

31
00:01:54,515 --> 00:01:56,885
What did I sign up for?

32
00:01:56,955 --> 00:02:00,395
I just know if you start a job
 then finish it.

33
00:02:00,476 --> 00:02:04,135
The onIy way to get smarter
is by playing a smarter opponent.

34
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:07,776
So, you have to come in connection
with a proper agent

35
00:02:08,004 --> 00:02:13,897
who knows your identity,
your reality potential.

36
00:02:13,897 --> 00:02:16,646
And can …
under their guidance

37
00:02:16,646 --> 00:02:19,676
you can engage
in self-discovery,

38
00:02:19,676 --> 00:02:22,956
self-realisation,
self-actualisation.

39
00:02:23,426 --> 00:02:28,101
You’ve heard their voice for so long,
you believe it to be you.

40
00:02:28,146 --> 00:02:31,206
You believe it
to be your best friend.

41
00:02:32,805 --> 00:02:35,197
They should believe
their opponent to be their best friend.

42
00:02:35,197 --> 00:02:37,675
Where’s the best place
an opponent should hide?

43
00:02:39,305 --> 00:02:42,224
In the very last place
you would ever look.

44
00:02:42,599 --> 00:02:46,898
He’s aII up here,
pretending to be you.

45
00:02:46,978 --> 00:02:51,159
We have met the enemy
and the enemy is us.

46
00:02:51,177 --> 00:02:53,380
[Laughing]

47
00:02:53,380 --> 00:02:55,406
Which is the actual truth.

48
00:02:55,406 --> 00:02:58,129
I’ve had enough of this shit.
TeII him you’ve had enough.

49
00:02:58,129 --> 00:03:00,243
—He tells you what to do …

50
00:03:00,243 --> 00:03:02,848
—Look, that’s enough.
—… and when to do it.

51
00:03:02,848 --> 00:03:04,589
—TeII him.
—I said that’s enough.

52
00:03:04,589 --> 00:03:08,579
Eventually, when the opponent
is challenged or questioned,

53
00:03:08,581 --> 00:03:13,900
it means the victim’s investment
and thus his intelligence is questioned.

54
00:03:14,179 --> 00:03:15,935
No one can accept that,

55
00:03:17,395 --> 00:03:19,095
not even to themselves.

56
00:03:21,435 --> 00:03:27,900
We are the enemy—the mind 
that we think is our friend.

57
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:33,495
And right now, he’s telling you 
that he doesn’t even exist.

58
00:03:33,885 --> 00:03:37,585
We just put you to war
with the onIy enemy that ever existed,

59
00:03:37,673 --> 00:03:41,023
and you, you think
he’s your best friend.

60
00:03:41,085 --> 00:03:42,575
That’s why,
day one—

61
00:03:42,575 --> 00:03:44,873
what does Guru Mahārāj
say to Gurudev?

62
00:03:44,873 --> 00:03:49,010
“Are you prepared to listen to me
and not your mind?”

63
00:03:49,010 --> 00:03:51,963
It’s the first thing he says him
because he knows:

64
00:03:51,963 --> 00:03:54,244
if that’s not at the basis
of the relationship,

65
00:03:54,244 --> 00:03:56,423
it’s going 
to be meaningless.

66
00:03:56,423 --> 00:03:57,623
He’s not going 
to make progress,

67
00:03:57,623 --> 00:03:59,864
he’s not going 
to go very far.

68
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:05,313
It’s going to be a show
of servitude, submission, discipleship.

69
00:04:05,313 --> 00:04:07,204
“But if you’re going
to follow me

70
00:04:07,204 --> 00:04:10,844
and resist the suggestions
of your mind,

71
00:04:10,844 --> 00:04:12,754
then you’re going 
to make progress.”

72
00:04:13,045 --> 00:04:16,419
Thank God we are not our minds!

73
00:04:16,419 --> 00:04:17,399
[Laughing]

